    {
      "id": "facility-reservation",
      "title": "Facility Reservation",
      "description": "It was my first project using Laravel (it is actually two applications at once, the other one is Asset Management).",
      "paragraphs": [
        "I remembered when I first get a task to build a Facility Reservation for Purwakarta District Government (from work, we are application's vendor), It was my first time discovered Livewire and I was very excited to try it.",
        "This also the time when Laravel 8 first released and introduced blade-component (I think) and I was super excited of these new technologies, so I built this with a struggle (because I never really tried Laravel on a real projects before just for learning purposes).",
        "It was not my proudest project I've ever been working on because I never really use or understand blade-component and it makes my code messy and there was so much repetition for an element (see the images for context).\nBut this project make me want to use Laravel even more, to learn and really try to understand it correctly by implementing best practices, etc.",
        "In purwakarta district government area, there are so much buildings and rooms in each of them, they used to write who's going to use the buildings or rooms on the whiteboard, for example, if the governor want to use \"A\" Building or \"B\" Hall, they (administration) write the date and time on the whiteboard, this app is a digitalized version of what they've used to do."
      ],
      "tags": [
        "PHP",
        "Laravel"
      ],
