    {
      "id": "asset-management",
      "title": "Asset Management",
      "description": "One of my first project with Laravel alongside the Facility Reservation app, but I was using <a href=\"https://github.com/rappasoft/laravel-boilerplate\" target=\"_blank\">Laravel Boilerplate</a> instead Livewire.",
      "paragraphs": [
        "When I built this app, I wasn't quite sure how to use and implement Laravel best practices, so my first thought was, \"I need a boilerplate\", then I found <a href=\"https://github.com/rappasoft/laravel-boilerplate\" target=\"_blank\">Laravel Boilerplate</a> when I was searching on the internet.",
        "Without any hesitation I tried this package, it already comes with user management, logs viewer and most importantly, the role and permissions. It was a time saver, I can't even imagine how long will it take me to build those features from the ground, probably it will take me forever, because I am quite new to Laravel back then.",
        "In purwakarta district government area, there are so much stuff that belongs to the government's assets, they want to keep an eye on those stuff, like chairs, air conditioners, etc. Besides this app, there comes with another Android App that scans RFIDs, we have a special device to scan them. After the devices scanned those RFIDs it send those scanned RFIDs to API and store it inside Database. In this app there is a feature that you can get those stored RFID's and mass assign it to the chosen asset and store it as an additional quantity.",
        "But after all, it was a fun project to work with, and I learned so much from it."
      ],
      "tags": [
        "PHP",
        "Laravel"
      ],
