    {
      "id": "handovers-and-filing",
      "title": "Handovers and Filing",
      "description": "One of my side project, my first time using Laravel jetstream.",
      "paragraphs": [
        "What this app does is store all the handovers and mass assign them to the chosen transporter, because my friend is work at the fulfillment providers they need a way to keep awb (airway bill) on the track, it's like mapping the items to the transporter. I almost forgot about filing, it's just an uploaded image of file and store it inside the application so they can see it in case the files or papers are gone.",
        "This is one of my side project my friend asked me to built, I really never used jetstream before but I really want to try it, I built this application using Laravel jetstream package (livewire) and at first I was really confuse and at the same time I learned how to use blade-component and other stuff correctly."
      ],
